502
00:37:08,295 --> 00:37:10,650
...who'd be the main character
in this book?

503
00:37:17,335 --> 00:37:19,690
Have you written up cases
like this before?

504
00:37:19,935 --> 00:37:21,891
A few of them for <i>Esquire,</i> yeah.

505
00:37:22,135 --> 00:37:23,363
What do you think?

506
00:37:23,615 --> 00:37:24,843
What do I think?

507
00:37:25,295 --> 00:37:28,332
If you're worried about the D.A.,
grand juries read papers.

508
00:37:28,575 --> 00:37:30,850
Proper spin control
could make a big difference.

509
00:37:31,095 --> 00:37:32,926
What the hell are you talking about?

510
00:37:33,175 --> 00:37:35,973
You said Hanson was a street hustler.
Did he have a record?

511
00:37:36,215 --> 00:37:38,012
Take drugs?
Deal drugs? Pimp?

512
00:37:38,255 --> 00:37:40,485
That kind of spin
can influence a grand jury.

513
00:37:40,735 --> 00:37:42,373
Get investigators to hit the streets.

514
00:37:42,615 --> 00:37:45,288
Every P.I. In town's an off-duty cop.

515
00:37:45,815 --> 00:37:48,454
Besides, why would we need a P. I...

516
00:37:48,695 --> 00:37:51,812
...when we got ourselves
a hotshot New York writer...

517
00:37:52,055 --> 00:37:53,807
...filling all the gaps?

518
00:37:56,175 --> 00:37:57,494
Take care, bubba.

519
00:38:17,455 --> 00:38:19,446
- Are you the flower man?
- No, I'm John Kelso.

520
00:38:19,695 --> 00:38:21,925
Good morning, I'm a writer
and wanted to ask you...

521
00:38:22,175 --> 00:38:24,564
If you're not the flower man,
leave me be.

522
00:38:24,815 --> 00:38:28,569
The Lady's in mourning, and
I haven't received a flower or a rose...

523
00:38:28,815 --> 00:38:31,727
...or anything to show for it.
Please leave me be.

524
00:38:35,215 --> 00:38:39,049
I know Billy Hanson used to live here.
I wanted to ask a few questions.

525
00:38:39,295 --> 00:38:41,968
And if it's an inappropriate time,
I'll come back later.

526
00:38:42,215 --> 00:38:46,891
I can't believe you're running around
ringing my doorbell. Where you from?

527
00:38:47,215 --> 00:38:48,887
Where are your manners?

528
00:38:49,135 --> 00:38:50,887
Just leave me be.

529
00:38:53,615 --> 00:38:55,731
My condolences.
I'll call...

530
00:38:56,495 --> 00:38:58,725
I'll come back another time, or...

531
00:40:22,575 --> 00:40:24,964
I apologize for the delay.

532
00:40:26,735 --> 00:40:31,445
Why, thank you. They're lovely.
They're absolutely lovely.

533
00:40:31,695 --> 00:40:34,414
I'd love to ask you a few questions,
if you have a minute.

534
00:40:34,895 --> 00:40:36,613
Is this your car?

535
00:40:38,575 --> 00:40:40,133
How about a ride home?

536
00:40:44,135 --> 00:40:45,250
Thank you.

537
00:40:53,895 --> 00:40:56,967
What I want to know is,
what is a white boy like you...

538
00:40:57,215 --> 00:41:01,527
...doing driving a big old brother's
jive-ass heap like this shit here?

539
00:41:01,775 --> 00:41:04,926
I just bought this.
I kind of like it. It's not a bad car.

540
00:41:05,175 --> 00:41:07,769
No, it's not bad.
Did I hurt your feelings?

541
00:41:08,015 --> 00:41:10,609
I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to hurt your feelings.

542
00:41:10,855 --> 00:41:14,165
I can't help it.
I just call things out as I see it.

543
00:41:14,415 --> 00:41:16,292
I just can't help it.
I just do that.

544
00:41:16,775 --> 00:41:19,209
- One thing you needn't worry about.
- What's that?

545
00:41:19,455 --> 00:41:23,004
Ain't nobody going to try
to steal this piece of shit.

546
00:41:23,655 --> 00:41:26,965
I'm just practicing up till I can save
enough money to get my Rolls.

547
00:41:27,215 --> 00:41:30,013
Chablis is a pretty name.
It's unusual.

548
00:41:30,255 --> 00:41:34,328
Thank you. I got it off a wine bottle.
It's a show name.

549
00:41:34,575 --> 00:41:38,284
- You're an actress?
- I'm not an actress. I'm a showgirl.

550
00:41:38,535 --> 00:41:40,969
I work at the Pick-Up on Congress.

551
00:41:41,215 --> 00:41:44,890
I lip-synch, I emcee, I dance.
You know, shit like that.

552
00:41:45,135 --> 00:41:48,889
The person you see now
is just little old simple Chablis.

553
00:41:49,135 --> 00:41:50,454
But in the evenings...

554
00:41:50,695 --> 00:41:53,926
...when I put on my gowns
and my makeup...

555
00:41:54,175 --> 00:41:56,769
...and my jewelry and my perfume...

556
00:41:57,015 --> 00:41:59,165
...I become "The Lady Chablis."

557
00:42:01,575 --> 00:42:03,930
You are just so cute.

558
00:42:04,175 --> 00:42:06,450
A cool white wine for a cool black girl.

559
00:42:06,695 --> 00:42:09,732
And you're full of flattery too.

560
00:42:10,535 --> 00:42:14,892
It's getting hot up in here, honey.
My shots are kicking in.

561
00:42:16,415 --> 00:42:17,325
Excuse me?

562
00:42:17,575 --> 00:42:20,089
Yes, honey, my shots.
Never mind that.

563
00:42:20,335 --> 00:42:22,405
What'd you want to talk to me about?

564
00:42:23,935 --> 00:42:25,050
Billy Hanson.

565
00:42:26,975 --> 00:42:30,570
No. Billy's dead.
Case closed.

566
00:42:31,175 --> 00:42:32,574
Was he your boyfriend?

567
00:42:32,815 --> 00:42:34,328
Billy, my boyfriend?

568
00:42:34,575 --> 00:42:35,974
Were you two lovers?

569
00:42:36,775 --> 00:42:38,003
No. Hell, no.

570
00:42:38,255 --> 00:42:41,053
Billy was way too trashy for me, honey.
I'm a lady.

571
00:42:41,295 --> 00:42:43,934
However, he did date
my roommate Corinne for a while.

572
00:42:45,455 --> 00:42:49,084
The two of those
had some wild times together.

573
00:42:53,135 --> 00:42:56,445
- Those are beautiful.
- So, tell me more about Corinne.

574
00:42:57,175 --> 00:42:59,450
Corinne's like a lot of girls.

575
00:43:00,055 --> 00:43:03,286
She found herself attracted
to the wrong type of man.

576
00:43:04,095 --> 00:43:07,804
Billy was not the right type of man.
She thought she could change him.

577
00:43:08,055 --> 00:43:11,252
But there was no way of changing
that evil son of a bitch.

578
00:43:11,495 --> 00:43:13,963
- I'd love to speak to Corinne.
- I'd like to too.

579
00:43:14,215 --> 00:43:18,288
But she skipped town
owing me two months' rent.

580
00:43:18,535 --> 00:43:21,368
And Billy said he would pay for it,
but now he's...

581
00:43:23,895 --> 00:43:25,533
But you know...

582
00:43:25,775 --> 00:43:27,845
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

583
00:43:28,095 --> 00:43:30,814
But you know,
it's like my mama always said...

584
00:43:32,895 --> 00:43:34,851
..."Two tears in a bucket...

585
00:43:35,095 --> 00:43:37,211
...motherfuck it."

586
00:43:38,535 --> 00:43:39,888
I have to remember that one.

587
00:43:40,135 --> 00:43:42,410
Don't remember that one.
That's off-the-record.

588
00:43:50,055 --> 00:43:51,534
Let me get your door for you.

589
00:44:04,655 --> 00:44:06,088
Thank you, hon.

590
00:44:11,855 --> 00:44:15,643
In the phone book,
you were listed as F. De Veau.

591
00:44:17,575 --> 00:44:19,133
What's the "F" stand for?

592
00:44:20,975 --> 00:44:23,364
The "F" stands for Frank, hon.

593
00:44:23,615 --> 00:44:24,843
That's me.

594
00:44:38,855 --> 00:44:40,686
- She's a he.
- Correct.

595
00:44:40,855 --> 00:44:42,129
You're shitting me.

596
00:44:42,375 --> 00:44:45,094
If this thing heats up,
I think you'll want to talk to her.

597
00:44:45,335 --> 00:44:47,166
Proper folks don't discuss such things.

598
00:44:47,615 --> 00:44:49,446
She paints a rotten picture of Billy.

599
00:44:49,695 --> 00:44:52,846
Let me tell you a story.
There was a judge here years ago.

600
00:44:53,095 --> 00:44:56,565
His oldest boy was messing around
with a gangster's girlfriend.

601
00:44:57,535 --> 00:44:59,412
One morning they found him...

602
00:45:00,055 --> 00:45:03,445
...lying under the porch
with his privates tucked into his lapel.

603
00:45:05,815 --> 00:45:07,806
Dead men tell no tales.

604
00:45:08,695 --> 00:45:10,686
Next day, headline read...

605
00:45:10,935 --> 00:45:12,766
..."Fall From Porch Proves Fatal."

606
00:45:13,975 --> 00:45:15,806
Some fall.
What's your point?

607
00:45:16,415 --> 00:45:20,533
Saving face in the light of unpleasant
circumstances is the Savannah way.

608
00:45:21,975 --> 00:45:24,614
I'll try to track down that real girl.
Corinne, you said?

609
00:45:25,215 --> 00:45:26,933
Well, I got to skedaddle.

610
00:45:27,175 --> 00:45:30,133
Doing Christmas at Tybee Island.
We got all sorts of folks coming.

611
00:45:30,375 --> 00:45:31,694
Have a great Christmas.

612
00:45:31,935 --> 00:45:34,290
- You too, John.
- See you later, Uga.

613
00:45:43,135 --> 00:45:45,171
<i>Merry Christmas!</i>

614
00:46:27,375 --> 00:46:28,933
He's got it on a string!

615
00:46:50,855 --> 00:46:52,413
Luther's not eating!

616
00:47:00,495 --> 00:47:01,689
Check, please.

617
00:47:03,015 --> 00:47:04,334
You didn't like it?

618
00:47:04,775 --> 00:47:07,050
No, they were very good.
Excellent.

619
00:47:09,495 --> 00:47:10,894
What was in the vial?

620
00:47:12,495 --> 00:47:15,692
He says it's enough poison
to kill everybody in the county.

621
00:47:17,495 --> 00:47:19,451
If he eats and it's a good day...

622
00:47:19,695 --> 00:47:20,605
...fine.

623
00:47:21,295 --> 00:47:22,410
If he doesn't eat...

624
00:47:22,655 --> 00:47:26,933
...let's put it this way: If I were
you, I wouldn't drink the water today.

625
00:47:27,335 --> 00:47:28,848
Where does he put the poison?

626
00:47:29,095 --> 00:47:31,404
In the water supply system.

627
00:47:33,775 --> 00:47:35,208
Is that true?
Do you believe that?

628
00:47:37,255 --> 00:47:41,646
I've lived here a long time, honey.
I believe most anything about anybody.

629
00:47:45,135 --> 00:47:46,409
Where are we going?

630
00:47:46,655 --> 00:47:48,532
Patience, dear boy.

631
00:47:52,895 --> 00:47:56,774
It's time you meet the most important
member of my defense team.

632
00:47:57,255 --> 00:47:58,654
We're going to the cemetery?

633
00:47:58,895 --> 00:48:02,365
Not Bonaventure.
The colored cemetery's down the road.

634
00:49:03,255 --> 00:49:06,292
Looks like we got the garden
all to ourselves tonight.

635
00:49:08,935 --> 00:49:10,334
Meet Minerva.

636
00:49:13,335 --> 00:49:14,290
How do you do?

637
00:49:15,975 --> 00:49:17,693
You trying to work me, boy?

638
00:49:18,975 --> 00:49:21,045
Put that hand back in your pocket.

639
00:49:28,535 --> 00:49:30,491
I feel sorry for you.

640
00:49:31,295 --> 00:49:32,887
Do tell, Minerva.

641
00:49:33,375 --> 00:49:35,286
He think nobody love him.

642
00:49:38,815 --> 00:49:40,533
That's silly.
We've never met.

643
00:49:43,415 --> 00:49:44,814
You got a hole in you.

644
00:49:45,055 --> 00:49:46,613
Too many questions.

645
00:49:46,855 --> 00:49:50,973
Don't know whether to be this way
or that without the answers.

646
00:49:53,175 --> 00:49:55,735
There ain't no answers.

647
00:50:00,935 --> 00:50:04,211
You come a long way to find that out,
didn't you?

648
00:50:07,175 --> 00:50:09,973
Now we got to get to work.
You bring the money?

649
00:50:12,255 --> 00:50:13,324
Put it on the grave.

650
00:50:15,655 --> 00:50:18,169
Kiss it first,
so it come back to you.

651
00:50:20,535 --> 00:50:22,685
You bring the shiny dimes?

652
00:50:29,735 --> 00:50:30,850
Bury them.

653
00:50:31,975 --> 00:50:34,967
He's working hard against you, James.

654
00:50:35,255 --> 00:50:36,893
Who? Dr. Buzzard?

655
00:50:39,135 --> 00:50:41,171
The boy. The dead boy.

656
00:50:41,695 --> 00:50:43,686
Oh, Billy.
That doesn't surprise us.

657
00:50:43,935 --> 00:50:45,334
Dr. Buzzard?

658
00:50:47,415 --> 00:50:48,848
Ain't got much dead time left.

659
00:50:49,895 --> 00:50:51,089
Dead time?

660
00:50:51,975 --> 00:50:53,533
Lasts an hour.

661
00:50:53,855 --> 00:50:57,086
Half-hour before midnight
till half past.

662
00:50:57,535 --> 00:51:00,413
Half-hour before midnight
for working good.

663
00:51:00,735 --> 00:51:02,805
Half-hour after for evil.

664
00:51:03,055 --> 00:51:05,250
We'll need a little of both tonight.

665
00:51:05,535 --> 00:51:07,127
You got the bottle of water?

666
00:51:09,455 --> 00:51:11,173
Ain't been through no pipe?

667
00:51:12,455 --> 00:51:13,729
Give it to me.

668
00:51:18,495 --> 00:51:20,008
We got to make him...

669
00:51:20,255 --> 00:51:23,167
...Ioosen up on James.

670
00:51:26,895 --> 00:51:28,214
I need Shango...

671
00:51:28,895 --> 00:51:30,965
...and a little <i>hungan.</i>

672
00:51:43,855 --> 00:51:44,890
Come.

673
00:51:46,295 --> 00:51:47,410
Come!

674
00:51:52,375 --> 00:51:54,286
Tell me something about him.

675
00:51:55,095 --> 00:51:56,494
He tried to kill me?

676
00:51:56,735 --> 00:51:59,124
No, before then.
Something good.

677
00:52:00,935 --> 00:52:02,050
Your kind words...

678
00:52:02,295 --> 00:52:04,763
...take root, flower,
come back to bless you.

679
00:52:06,135 --> 00:52:07,966
Something that made him happy?

680
00:52:11,455 --> 00:52:12,570
His Camaro.

681
00:52:13,295 --> 00:52:15,934
He loved his Camaro.
He wouldn't let anyone near it.

682
00:52:16,175 --> 00:52:18,325
That car was his pride and joy.

683
00:52:18,975 --> 00:52:21,170
Keep talking. It's working.
It's working!

684
00:52:22,695 --> 00:52:25,653
He spray painted it flat black.

685
00:52:25,895 --> 00:52:29,171
You should've seen him.
He spent hours on that car, fixing it...

686
00:52:29,415 --> 00:52:30,370
...cleaning it.

687
00:52:30,615 --> 00:52:32,810
He painted racing stripes on it...

688
00:52:33,055 --> 00:52:34,773
...and all kinds of other things.

689
00:52:35,455 --> 00:52:36,888
He was very creative.

690
00:52:39,575 --> 00:52:41,725
That's something
most people didn't know.

691
00:52:41,975 --> 00:52:43,374
He was an artist.

692
00:52:44,135 --> 00:52:46,603
Just now,
when you were saying them things...

693
00:52:46,855 --> 00:52:48,846
...I felt him ease off.

694
00:52:49,655 --> 00:52:51,691
He heard you say you love him.

695
00:52:54,815 --> 00:52:57,329
That's preposterous.
He tried to kill me.

696
00:52:59,615 --> 00:53:02,004
He was working against you,
and now I know why.

697
00:53:02,415 --> 00:53:05,691
He wants you to tell the whole world
you hated him.

698
00:53:06,695 --> 00:53:09,004
Maybe they think you hated him
enough to kill him.

699
00:53:09,735 --> 00:53:11,691
If you do that, you go to jail...

700
00:53:11,935 --> 00:53:13,209
...and he know that.

701
00:53:14,815 --> 00:53:16,646
Most important thing:

702
00:53:17,735 --> 00:53:21,694
You got to beg that boy's forgiveness
each and every day.

703
00:53:27,455 --> 00:53:29,286
Time for evil.

704
00:53:34,015 --> 00:53:36,449
Quick, quick.
Tell me his name.

705
00:53:36,935 --> 00:53:38,334
Finley Largent.

706
00:53:38,975 --> 00:53:43,526
When you get home, write his name
7 times on a piece of paper.

707
00:53:43,775 --> 00:53:45,766
Connect all the names into one.

708
00:53:46,015 --> 00:53:48,051
Dot no I's, cross no T's.

709
00:53:48,335 --> 00:53:50,610
Fold it twice and put it in your pocket.

710
00:53:54,975 --> 00:53:56,090
Get a picture.

711
00:53:56,335 --> 00:53:59,054
Sew up the mouth with dove's blood.

712
00:53:59,295 --> 00:54:00,444
Blacken the eyes.

713
00:54:00,695 --> 00:54:02,731
Now go!
I got works to do.

714
00:54:06,695 --> 00:54:07,730
Boy!

715
00:54:08,615 --> 00:54:10,333
Take these words to heart.

716
00:54:12,335 --> 00:54:14,485
To understand the living...

717
00:54:14,815 --> 00:54:17,283
...you got to commune with the dead.

718
00:54:20,615 --> 00:54:21,525
Now go!

719
00:54:21,775 --> 00:54:23,572
And don't you dare look back!

720
00:54:53,615 --> 00:54:54,968
On the grave...

721
00:54:55,335 --> 00:54:56,973
Who is Dr. Buzzard?

722
00:54:57,255 --> 00:54:59,211
Minerva was married to Dr. Buzzard...

723
00:54:59,455 --> 00:55:02,845
...the foremost voodoo practitioner
in Beaufort County.

724
00:55:03,095 --> 00:55:05,893
You may not know it,
but you are deep in voodoo country.

725
00:55:06,655 --> 00:55:08,964
I don't believe
in the hocus-pocus of it...

726
00:55:09,215 --> 00:55:11,604
...but the spiritual force behind it.

727
00:55:12,215 --> 00:55:15,013
The shiny dimes were easy...

728
00:55:15,255 --> 00:55:17,928
...but the virgin water
was a trick or two.

729
00:55:18,575 --> 00:55:21,453
How do you know she wouldn't know
the difference if it was tap water?

730
00:55:22,575 --> 00:55:24,406
Not by looking or taste...

731
00:55:24,655 --> 00:55:27,453
...but she would've known
in an instant by looking at my face.

732
00:55:32,575 --> 00:55:33,769
I think...

733
00:55:34,015 --> 00:55:36,813
...the photo-doctoring
is going to be good therapy.

734
00:55:38,935 --> 00:55:41,403
What about the pleas
for daily forgiveness?

735
00:55:42,655 --> 00:55:46,534
No, I don't think that's
going to be happening. Definitely not.

736
00:55:54,335 --> 00:55:55,848
- Thank you.
- Have a good day.

737
00:55:57,175 --> 00:55:58,574
- Hey, you.
- How are you?

738
00:55:58,815 --> 00:55:59,964
- How you doing?
- Good.

739
00:56:00,215 --> 00:56:01,170
You work here?

740
00:56:01,655 --> 00:56:03,327
What you see is what you get.

741
00:56:03,575 --> 00:56:04,803
Nothing wrong with that.

742
00:56:05,055 --> 00:56:06,568
Gee, thanks.

743
00:56:25,335 --> 00:56:26,563
These are nice.

744
00:56:27,015 --> 00:56:29,006
You want to send some flowers?

745
00:56:30,135 --> 00:56:32,285
I think so.
I don't know, though.

746
00:56:32,535 --> 00:56:34,014
It's kind of complicated.

747
00:56:34,615 --> 00:56:35,889
For whom?

748
00:56:36,815 --> 00:56:38,009
What's she like?

749
00:56:38,255 --> 00:56:40,007
I don't know her that well.

750
00:56:40,255 --> 00:56:41,449
Roses are a favorite.

751
00:56:41,695 --> 00:56:43,606
