Means Jim killed him in cold blood...

1001
01:11:52,855 --> 01:11:54,208
...mocked up the scene.

1002
01:11:54,455 --> 01:11:56,093
How you plan to counter that?

1003
01:11:56,455 --> 01:12:01,085
Gunshot residue test is unreliable.
It's inadmissable in some jurisdictions.

1004
01:12:01,335 --> 01:12:04,771
Finley's got Doc Poe. We will counter
with cutting-edge science...

1005
01:12:05,015 --> 01:12:07,404
...with an expert we got from up north.

1006
01:12:09,255 --> 01:12:12,327
They say the scene was contrived.
What do you say?

1007
01:12:12,695 --> 01:12:14,128
That's our silver bullet.

1008
01:12:15,055 --> 01:12:16,727
Shoddy police work.

1009
01:12:16,975 --> 01:12:18,488
Take a look at this.

1010
01:12:25,095 --> 01:12:26,448
That's me!

1011
01:12:26,695 --> 01:12:28,048
Just like you said.

1012
01:12:28,295 --> 01:12:30,729
Ground zero.
Cops should never have let you in.

1013
01:12:31,855 --> 01:12:34,574
I kind of let myself in
through the back gate.

1014
01:12:35,855 --> 01:12:37,971
They shouldn't have let you get in.

1015
01:12:39,535 --> 01:12:41,810
<i>Happy together</i>

1016
01:12:42,615 --> 01:12:45,049
<i>Unhappy together</i>

1017
01:12:45,815 --> 01:12:48,010
<i>And won 't it be fine</i>

1018
01:12:53,095 --> 01:12:56,132
<i>Days may be cloudy or sunny</i>

1019
01:12:59,175 --> 01:13:02,804
<i>We're in or we're out of the money</i>

1020
01:13:06,935 --> 01:13:08,846
<i>But I'm with you always</i>

1021
01:13:10,895 --> 01:13:12,806
<i>Come rain or</i>

1022
01:13:14,775 --> 01:13:16,686
<i>Shine</i>

1023
01:13:27,335 --> 01:13:28,529
Joe Odom.

1024
01:13:32,295 --> 01:13:34,286
You're good.
I didn't know you sang.

1025
01:13:34,535 --> 01:13:35,888
- You never asked.
- How you doing?

1026
01:13:36,135 --> 01:13:37,363
Good, how are you?

1027
01:13:38,015 --> 01:13:41,212
- You got another set?
- No, me and Joe's just sitting in.

1028
01:13:41,455 --> 01:13:42,729
Want to get a cup of coffee?

1029
01:13:42,975 --> 01:13:44,727
Business or pleasure?

1030
01:13:45,095 --> 01:13:46,084
Come on.

1031
01:13:48,735 --> 01:13:53,286
Normally, there'd be no problem.
The general rule is rich people get off.

1032
01:13:53,535 --> 01:13:55,446
Problem is, they're usually straight.

1033
01:13:55,735 --> 01:13:57,805
See, so it's a volatile issue.

1034
01:13:58,055 --> 01:14:00,489
- I'm not crazy?
- No. Neither is Sonny.

1035
01:14:00,735 --> 01:14:02,532
Jim's friends knew he was gay.

1036
01:14:02,775 --> 01:14:06,563
Secretly, they congratulated themselves
on being so cosmopolitan.

1037
01:14:06,815 --> 01:14:11,525
If they knew he was completely open with
his sexuality, they'd have shunned him.

1038
01:14:11,975 --> 01:14:13,727
Maybe the jury will too.

1039
01:14:13,975 --> 01:14:14,851
You think?

1040
01:14:16,695 --> 01:14:19,846
Of course, no one'll ever really know
what happened that night.

1041
01:14:20,095 --> 01:14:22,848
But Jim's told the story
a thousand times, never wavered.

1042
01:14:23,095 --> 01:14:24,767
You're quite the advocate.

1043
01:14:25,015 --> 01:14:28,644
What happened to
"Stick around and stay objective"?

1044
01:14:28,895 --> 01:14:32,490
Objectively, it's looking like
they'll hang him for his sexuality.

1045
01:14:32,735 --> 01:14:35,329
Something that would never happen
in New York, right?

1046
01:14:36,695 --> 01:14:38,970
Well, you said it, not me.

1047
01:14:41,095 --> 01:14:42,767
You don't seem like you're from here.

1048
01:14:43,015 --> 01:14:45,449
I was born here, didn't like it...

1049
01:14:45,695 --> 01:14:46,810
...moved away.

1050
01:14:47,055 --> 01:14:49,125
Figured out the part
I didn't like was me.

1051
01:14:49,375 --> 01:14:52,173
So I worked on that,
and I moved back.

1052
01:14:54,175 --> 01:14:55,767
I got my first kiss right here.

1053
01:14:56,015 --> 01:14:58,449
Sammy Jenks.
Gave him a black eye.

1054
01:14:58,695 --> 01:15:00,413
You did? How hard?

1055
01:15:03,055 --> 01:15:04,488
That's what love'll do.

1056
01:15:04,975 --> 01:15:09,446
I have trouble picturing what kind of
woman you'd take the trouble to marry.

1057
01:15:12,855 --> 01:15:14,493
First love situation.

1058
01:15:15,135 --> 01:15:19,208
We got married a week after graduating
college, if you can believe that.

1059
01:15:19,455 --> 01:15:20,683
So what happened?

1060
01:15:20,935 --> 01:15:22,527
You want to hear my sob story?

1061
01:15:22,775 --> 01:15:26,006
I think she thought
she was marrying Norman Mailer.

1062
01:15:26,855 --> 01:15:28,527
She thought I'd be famous.

1063
01:15:29,095 --> 01:15:33,566
After the book was published, she'd wake
up at the crack of dawn on Sunday...

1064
01:15:33,815 --> 01:15:36,045
...make coffee, cross her fingers...

1065
01:15:36,295 --> 01:15:39,446
...and look in that Sunday <i>Times,</i>
sure it was going to be a bestseller.

1066
01:15:39,815 --> 01:15:43,854
One Sunday, she didn't wake up early,
didn't make coffee...

1067
01:15:44,095 --> 01:15:45,926
...didn't cross her fingers...

1068
01:15:47,095 --> 01:15:48,289
...and I knew.

1069
01:15:49,335 --> 01:15:52,008
She left you
because your book wasn't a hit?

1070
01:15:52,775 --> 01:15:56,245
I don't know, Kelso.
It seems pretty shallow to me.

1071
01:15:58,295 --> 01:15:59,967
What about you and Joe Odom?

1072
01:16:00,975 --> 01:16:02,374
Me and Joe.

1073
01:16:02,615 --> 01:16:04,253
We're just friends.

1074
01:16:04,615 --> 01:16:07,129
We have a real musical relationship.

1075
01:16:07,695 --> 01:16:10,892
We're like the Steve and Eydie
of Savannah.

1076
01:16:16,375 --> 01:16:18,127
My God, it's quiet.

1077
01:16:18,495 --> 01:16:19,405
Too quiet.

1078
01:16:19,655 --> 01:16:22,169
Joe'll be playing at that bar
until dawn.

1079
01:16:27,335 --> 01:16:28,768
I should probably go.

1080
01:16:34,975 --> 01:16:39,253
In case you're wondering,
this is the perfect time for a kiss.

1081
01:16:40,575 --> 01:16:42,645
Sammy Jenks warned me about you.

1082
01:17:02,175 --> 01:17:03,244
Good night.

1083
01:17:10,535 --> 01:17:14,164
Ladies and gentlemen,
you constitute our jury for this trial.

1084
01:17:14,415 --> 01:17:16,167
It's expected to last several days.

1085
01:17:16,415 --> 01:17:18,087
I'll let you go home for the evening...

1086
01:17:18,335 --> 01:17:22,374
...instruct you to be back
in the morning at 9:30 in the jury room.

1087
01:17:22,615 --> 01:17:25,368
If anybody tries to approach you
about this case...

1088
01:17:25,615 --> 01:17:28,083
...report it to me
the first thing in the morning.

1089
01:17:28,655 --> 01:17:30,532
You're excused for the evening.

1090
01:17:33,415 --> 01:17:35,929
Mr. Driggers, let me speak to you.

1091
01:17:41,615 --> 01:17:43,287
Luther, listen.

1092
01:17:43,535 --> 01:17:46,845
This is a courtroom. Don't bring
those flies in here tomorrow.

1093
01:17:47,175 --> 01:17:51,805
And leave that vial of water,
or whatever that stuff is, at home.

1094
01:17:52,415 --> 01:17:53,564
Sam...

1095
01:17:53,895 --> 01:17:57,888
...you know, when we were in Georgia,
I know how you hated my bugs...

1096
01:17:58,135 --> 01:17:59,853
...and you know how I love them.

1097
01:18:00,455 --> 01:18:02,810
We're no longer at the university.
This is a courtroom.

1098
01:18:03,055 --> 01:18:06,525
I'm telling you to leave
all that foolishness at home.

1099
01:18:07,535 --> 01:18:09,571
I do take umbrage.

1100
01:18:10,055 --> 01:18:11,534
But I'll do it.

1101
01:18:12,655 --> 01:18:15,215
What is the story with the guy
with the horsefly epaulets?

1102
01:18:15,455 --> 01:18:16,888
Luther Driggers.

1103
01:18:17,135 --> 01:18:18,329
He's a genius.

1104
01:18:18,575 --> 01:18:20,566
Developed the "No-Bug" strip.

1105
01:18:20,815 --> 01:18:23,568
The company he worked for
took the credit and the money.

1106
01:18:23,815 --> 01:18:26,966
Now he just wanders around town
with a bottle of poison in his pocket.

1107
01:18:27,215 --> 01:18:28,091
Of course.

1108
01:18:28,335 --> 01:18:32,010
Says someday he's going to put it
in the water supply, do us all in.

1109
01:18:32,255 --> 01:18:33,927
Why do you want him on the jury?

1110
01:18:34,175 --> 01:18:37,212
We're the defense team.
We need all the nuts we can get.

1111
01:18:37,455 --> 01:18:38,854
What about Largent?

1112
01:18:39,175 --> 01:18:41,245
Finley's up for reelection.

1113
01:18:41,615 --> 01:18:42,889
If he strikes Luther...

1114
01:18:43,135 --> 01:18:44,773
...he might upset him enough to...

1115
01:18:45,615 --> 01:18:46,570
...you know...

1116
01:18:48,655 --> 01:18:50,566
I'll be back in on Sunday.

1117
01:18:51,335 --> 01:18:54,566
You've got a murder trial
starting in 3 days. Where you going?

1118
01:18:56,815 --> 01:18:58,851
Home opener against 'Bama.

1119
01:19:00,775 --> 01:19:02,208
Go, Dogs!

1120
01:19:05,055 --> 01:19:06,010
Is he really leaving?

1121
01:19:06,255 --> 01:19:07,973
Oh, yeah.
Better say a prayer.

1122
01:19:10,175 --> 01:19:11,449
All right, Mr. Largent...

1123
01:19:11,695 --> 01:19:15,131
...the state has the burden of proof,
and you have the opening.

1124
01:19:18,215 --> 01:19:19,284
Your Honor.

1125
01:19:22,655 --> 01:19:25,408
Good morning, Your Honor,
ladies and gentlemen of the jury.

1126
01:19:27,295 --> 01:19:30,685
The state of Georgia is ready
and most anxious to proceed.

1127
01:19:40,255 --> 01:19:41,893
If the court pleases.

1128
01:19:53,735 --> 01:19:56,090
The philosopher Thomas Hobbes
is quoted as saying...

1129
01:19:56,335 --> 01:19:57,734
...that life is...

1130
01:19:57,975 --> 01:19:59,806
...nasty, brutish...

1131
01:20:00,415 --> 01:20:01,609
...and short.

1132
01:20:03,335 --> 01:20:06,532
And surely it must have seemed so
to Billy Hanson...

1133
01:20:07,295 --> 01:20:09,047
...as he lay wounded...

1134
01:20:09,415 --> 01:20:11,724
...his blood and his life...

1135
01:20:11,975 --> 01:20:15,172
...oozing out
onto Jim Williams' Persian rug.

1136
01:20:17,415 --> 01:20:20,134
It's important for you to know
that the defendant...

1137
01:20:22,455 --> 01:20:24,207
By the end of this trial...

1138
01:20:24,735 --> 01:20:25,724
...I believe...

1139
01:20:26,455 --> 01:20:29,174
...that when faced with the evidence...

1140
01:20:29,695 --> 01:20:30,889
...you will render...

1141
01:20:31,135 --> 01:20:33,968
...the verdict that is fair and just:

1142
01:20:36,575 --> 01:20:38,770
Guilty of first-degree murder.

1143
01:20:44,055 --> 01:20:45,090
Thank you.

1144
01:20:54,295 --> 01:20:58,493
All right, Mr. Seiler,
we've been going for some time now.

1145
01:20:58,735 --> 01:21:02,250
Would you prefer to make
your opening statement after recess?

1146
01:21:05,335 --> 01:21:08,566
I would prefer to address
the jury now, Your Honor.

1147
01:21:11,415 --> 01:21:13,531
What I have to say won't take long.

1148
01:21:17,295 --> 01:21:19,331
I apologize if I look tired...

1149
01:21:20,615 --> 01:21:22,412
...if my eyes are red...

1150
01:21:23,135 --> 01:21:25,205
...if my complexion is sallow.

1151
01:21:25,975 --> 01:21:28,045
But I came by it honestly.

1152
01:21:29,135 --> 01:21:30,363
Because...

1153
01:21:30,615 --> 01:21:32,810
...I have not had much sleep lately.

1154
01:21:33,335 --> 01:21:35,610
For while my bed is soft...

1155
01:21:36,455 --> 01:21:38,650
...my client's is not.

1156
01:21:39,255 --> 01:21:42,531
And while I'm surrounded
by my loving family...

1157
01:21:43,495 --> 01:21:45,008
...Jim Williams...

1158
01:21:45,775 --> 01:21:47,094
...my friend...

1159
01:21:47,695 --> 01:21:48,923
...my client...

1160
01:21:50,215 --> 01:21:51,728
...is locked up in a room...

1161
01:21:51,975 --> 01:21:55,251
...full of thieves,
murderers and rapists.

1162
01:21:58,495 --> 01:22:00,008
You're the ones I want.

1163
01:22:00,895 --> 01:22:02,886
You're the ones I trust.

1164
01:22:04,255 --> 01:22:08,407
Because although it is Jim Williams
on trial here today...

1165
01:22:08,855 --> 01:22:11,369
...when I look at the circumstances...

1166
01:22:11,695 --> 01:22:13,367
...I think to myself...

1167
01:22:13,735 --> 01:22:14,690
...there...

1168
01:22:14,935 --> 01:22:17,733
...but for the grace of God,
go you...

1169
01:22:18,095 --> 01:22:19,050
...or I.

1170
01:22:19,735 --> 01:22:22,488
You know why?
Because I guaran-damn-tee you:

1171
01:22:22,735 --> 01:22:25,693
Someone comes into my home
and shoot at me, I will shoot back.

1172
01:22:25,935 --> 01:22:28,130
And I'll shoot back again and again...

1173
01:22:28,375 --> 01:22:30,889
...and again,
until I'm sure that they're dead.

1174
01:22:31,135 --> 01:22:35,367
Until I'm sure that my home
and my family are safe.

1175
01:22:39,855 --> 01:22:41,004
And then...

1176
01:22:41,775 --> 01:22:43,686
...old Finley here, my friend...

1177
01:22:44,335 --> 01:22:46,246
...would be prosecuting me.

1178
01:22:46,615 --> 01:22:48,412
I'd be the one on trial.

1179
01:22:48,975 --> 01:22:50,374
And my life...

1180
01:22:50,615 --> 01:22:52,014
...would be in the hands...

1181
01:22:52,655 --> 01:22:54,930
...of good folks like you.

1182
01:22:55,055 --> 01:22:57,091
He is way out-of-bounds.

1183
01:22:57,615 --> 01:23:01,449
He didn't object once during ours.
We'll look like assholes.

1184
01:23:01,695 --> 01:23:03,606
Folks not swayed by fancy words.

1185
01:23:04,295 --> 01:23:06,604
Folks who would not be prejudiced...

1186
01:23:07,695 --> 01:23:09,970
...who would not judge a man...

1187
01:23:10,215 --> 01:23:12,126
...by the color of his skin...

1188
01:23:12,735 --> 01:23:14,885
...or the amount of money that he makes.

1189
01:23:15,255 --> 01:23:16,404
I will say...

1190
01:23:17,015 --> 01:23:19,006
...the simple fact of the matter...

1191
01:23:19,255 --> 01:23:20,370
...is...

1192
01:23:21,175 --> 01:23:22,847
...Jim Williams...

1193
01:23:23,775 --> 01:23:25,766
...murdered no one.

1194
01:23:29,895 --> 01:23:32,489
How did you think it went?
Because I was very pleased.

1195
01:23:32,735 --> 01:23:35,693
Sonny has a certain style,
a flair, doesn't he?

1196
01:23:35,935 --> 01:23:37,084
From what I've seen...

1197
01:23:37,335 --> 01:23:40,213
...that man could weave horseshit
into Egyptian cotton.

1198
01:23:40,615 --> 01:23:42,571
Pleasantly surprised.

1199
01:23:43,615 --> 01:23:45,810
John Kelso,
I hope you understand.

1200
01:23:46,215 --> 01:23:48,046
Might I consider you my friend?

1201
01:23:49,615 --> 01:23:50,650
Yes.

1202
01:23:54,535 --> 01:23:58,369
The lack of gunshot residue in the hand,
plus the other things I mentioned...

1203
01:23:58,615 --> 01:24:01,368
...led me to the conclusion
that the scene was contrived.

1204
01:24:03,695 --> 01:24:05,413
Thank you, Detective Boone.

1205
01:24:05,655 --> 01:24:07,134
No further questions.

1206
01:24:09,735 --> 01:24:11,134
Detective...

1207
01:24:12,535 --> 01:24:15,732
...I'd like to revisit
some of the things...

1208
01:24:16,335 --> 01:24:18,849
...you said just then in direct.

1209
01:24:22,015 --> 01:24:25,849
You testified there was blood
on Hanson's hand, correct?

1210
01:24:26,095 --> 01:24:29,405
Yes. There was blood in the palm
of the victim's hand.

1211
01:24:29,895 --> 01:24:33,171
And that's important because if Hanson
had been holding the gun...

1212
01:24:33,415 --> 01:24:34,734
...there'd be no blood.

1213
01:24:36,855 --> 01:24:40,291
But you never saw the blood
on the victim's hand, did you?

1214
01:24:40,655 --> 01:24:41,610
No.

1215
01:24:42,615 --> 01:24:45,004
The blood was noted
in the autopsy report.

1216
01:24:45,255 --> 01:24:47,610
I didn't turn them over
when I bagged them.

1217
01:24:48,295 --> 01:24:50,650
I believe you also testified that...

1218
01:24:50,895 --> 01:24:55,571
...you believe the final shot was fired
from above the victim, is that correct?

1219
01:24:56,335 --> 01:25:00,328
I concluded that the shot came
from someone standing over the victim...

1220
01:25:00,655 --> 01:25:01,974
...execution style.

1221
01:25:04,455 --> 01:25:05,968
A <i>coup de grâce.</i>

1222
01:25:06,575 --> 01:25:08,008
A <i>coup de grâce</i>?

1223
01:25:15,375 --> 01:25:17,650
Will you tell the jury, please...

1224
01:25:18,615 --> 01:25:22,449
...did you find Jim's prints
on Billy's gun?

1225
01:25:26,095 --> 01:25:29,246
The Luger handle has a textured surface.

1226
01:25:30,855 --> 01:25:32,891
Is the answer no, Detective?

1227
01:25:33,855 --> 01:25:36,415
Yes, the answer was no.

1228
01:25:36,655 --> 01:25:38,532
Yes, the answer is no.

1229
01:25:39,935 --> 01:25:41,926
State's 22, Your Honor.

1230
01:25:45,935 --> 01:25:47,846
Who's this handsome fellow?

1231
01:25:48,135 --> 01:25:49,090
That's me.

1232
01:25:52,055 --> 01:25:53,568
Who's this?

1233
01:25:55,015 --> 01:25:57,575
That's that reporter fella
from up north.

1234
01:25:57,815 --> 01:26:00,045
The one that's working with Williams.

1235
01:26:00,655 --> 01:26:02,373
I don't know how he got in.

1236
01:26:02,815 --> 01:26:04,168
And this?

1237
01:26:04,975 --> 01:26:06,328
Young officer...

1238
01:26:06,575 --> 01:26:07,974
...name escapes me.

1239
01:26:08,215 --> 01:26:12,766
Understandable. You'd need a program
to keep track of everyone in that room.

1240
01:26:13,015 --> 01:26:14,209
Objection!

1241
01:26:14,455 --> 01:26:16,252
Counsel's testifying.

1242
01:26:16,655 --> 01:26:17,974
Strike that.

1243
01:26:18,615 --> 01:26:21,209
I would much rather have
the detective tell us.

1244
01:26:21,535 --> 01:26:23,890
How many people was in that room?

1245
01:26:25,255 --> 01:26:26,449
Seven.

1246
01:26:27,335 --> 01:26:28,324
No, eight.

1247
01:26:28,575 --> 01:26:31,647
"Seven, no, eight."
And a pussycat.

