01:43:04,076 --> 01:43:08,433
...on cross-examination they'll be
pretty rough on you and your background.

1499
01:43:08,676 --> 01:43:13,227
I have nothing to hide and I'm
not ashamed of anything I've ever done.

1500
01:43:13,476 --> 01:43:17,833
You should know that you taking the
stand is a blanket indictment of Hanson.

1501
01:43:18,076 --> 01:43:20,192
Let me get this right, now.

1502
01:43:20,436 --> 01:43:24,668
You're saying because Billy hung out
with drag queens, he deserved to die?

1503
01:43:24,916 --> 01:43:26,872
- It's fucked up, but, yeah.
- That's fucked up.

1504
01:43:28,996 --> 01:43:30,907
Maybe you shouldn't testify.

1505
01:43:31,956 --> 01:43:34,629
John, how sweet. You really care.

1506
01:43:35,476 --> 01:43:38,195
Good. Because, guess what?
I'm testifying.

1507
01:43:38,436 --> 01:43:39,949
I am testifying.

1508
01:43:40,196 --> 01:43:43,154
You see, those folks think
they're using the Doll...

1509
01:43:43,396 --> 01:43:45,307
...but the Doll's using them right back.

1510
01:43:45,556 --> 01:43:50,266
I'm going to use that courtroom
as my coming-out party.

1511
01:43:50,516 --> 01:43:51,949
You see, you know who I am.

1512
01:43:52,196 --> 01:43:54,426
I'm the Lady Chablis.

1513
01:43:54,676 --> 01:43:55,995
Hear me roar.

1514
01:43:56,236 --> 01:43:57,146
Look out!

1515
01:43:58,756 --> 01:44:01,031
Besides,
I've already bought a new ensemble.

1516
01:44:01,276 --> 01:44:03,710
- Really? Is it nice?
- You'll see, hon.

1517
01:44:04,196 --> 01:44:05,470
Listen to me.

1518
01:44:05,796 --> 01:44:07,388
We must get out of here.

1519
01:44:07,636 --> 01:44:10,594
It's rude of you to bust in on me.
I'd never do that to you.

1520
01:44:10,916 --> 01:44:13,111
LaVella's mother
is about to have a seizure.

1521
01:44:13,356 --> 01:44:16,075
Somebody put a spoon in her mouth, then,
because I'm not leaving.

1522
01:44:16,316 --> 01:44:17,465
You're leaving now.

1523
01:44:17,716 --> 01:44:19,388
- I am not.
- I'll buy you a drink.

1524
01:44:19,636 --> 01:44:20,785
- Buy me a drink.
- Outside of here.

1525
01:44:21,036 --> 01:44:22,708
- Buy me a diamond.
- I'll buy you a diamond.

1526
01:44:22,956 --> 01:44:24,867
- Give me some.
- I'm not giving you shit.

1527
01:44:25,116 --> 01:44:26,629
Oh, come on!

1528
01:44:26,876 --> 01:44:28,309
You know I'm straight.

1529
01:44:28,556 --> 01:44:29,625
So am I.

1530
01:44:29,876 --> 01:44:31,867
Straight to my house. Let's go.

1531
01:44:38,196 --> 01:44:39,311
Raise your right hand.

1532
01:44:39,556 --> 01:44:43,947
Do you swear the evidence you're about
to give is the truth, so help you God?

1533
01:44:44,196 --> 01:44:45,072
I do.

1534
01:44:47,196 --> 01:44:48,754
Now, Miss De Veau...

1535
01:44:49,276 --> 01:44:52,905
...I'll ask you a question and
I want you to answer to the jury...

1536
01:44:53,156 --> 01:44:56,228
...so that they can understand.

1537
01:44:57,956 --> 01:45:00,868
Yes, and what is that?
You'd like me to explain my "T"?

1538
01:45:01,436 --> 01:45:03,154
Your "T"?

1539
01:45:05,116 --> 01:45:06,435
My "T."

1540
01:45:06,676 --> 01:45:08,507
Yeah, explain your "T"...

1541
01:45:08,756 --> 01:45:12,795
...in as plain a language
as you possibly can for our friends.

1542
01:45:13,036 --> 01:45:16,153
I will try my best to explain
to you jurors.

1543
01:45:16,396 --> 01:45:19,513
I could throw words and labels
at all of you...

1544
01:45:19,756 --> 01:45:21,428
...but you seem like nice people.

1545
01:45:21,956 --> 01:45:24,186
So I'm going to be open and honest.

1546
01:45:25,476 --> 01:45:28,274
I have a man's toolbox...

1547
01:45:29,036 --> 01:45:31,152
...but everything else about me
is pure lady.

1548
01:45:32,676 --> 01:45:34,155
I love to dress in women's clothes.

1549
01:45:35,116 --> 01:45:37,072
I love to go shopping.

1550
01:45:37,316 --> 01:45:39,227
I love to have my nails done...

1551
01:45:39,476 --> 01:45:41,910
...and I love men.

1552
01:45:45,236 --> 01:45:46,908
Any questions?

1553
01:45:49,316 --> 01:45:51,830
And, ma'am,
I hope you don't mind my saying...

1554
01:45:52,116 --> 01:45:55,108
...blue is definitely not your color.

1555
01:45:55,396 --> 01:45:57,148
Okay, gals, you're both pretty, now.

1556
01:45:57,796 --> 01:46:01,186
What I want to know
and want you to tell the jury is...

1557
01:46:01,436 --> 01:46:03,950
...how you and Billy Hanson first met.

1558
01:46:04,796 --> 01:46:07,947
Billy hit on me one night at the...
Strike that, Your Honor.

1559
01:46:08,476 --> 01:46:09,704
Billy and I clienteled.

1560
01:46:10,076 --> 01:46:11,065
"Clienteled."

1561
01:46:11,316 --> 01:46:13,113
Will you explain what that means?

1562
01:46:13,356 --> 01:46:17,872
We socialized together for a little
while, until he met my roommate Corinne.

1563
01:46:18,116 --> 01:46:20,346
Corinne.
Now, you telling me that...

1564
01:46:20,596 --> 01:46:24,111
...Corinne and Billy Hanson
were intimate?

1565
01:46:25,516 --> 01:46:27,586
Hot and intimate.

1566
01:46:29,876 --> 01:46:31,707
Will you tell the jury...

1567
01:46:32,156 --> 01:46:33,908
...did Billy Hanson use drugs?

1568
01:46:37,636 --> 01:46:41,345
Yes. Billy did pills, smoked pot...

1569
01:46:41,596 --> 01:46:42,870
...little coke.

1570
01:46:43,116 --> 01:46:45,346
He sold drugs.

1571
01:46:45,796 --> 01:46:50,312
He'd stay with us sometimes, so
sometimes we had stash around the house.

1572
01:46:52,596 --> 01:46:54,666
- Mrs. Chablis...
- Miss.

1573
01:46:55,076 --> 01:46:57,067
Course, Miss Chablis.

1574
01:46:58,316 --> 01:47:00,068
Do you yourself take drugs?

1575
01:47:01,876 --> 01:47:03,867
I smoke a little pot.

1576
01:47:04,116 --> 01:47:06,027
I'm a mellow kind of girl.

1577
01:47:06,796 --> 01:47:07,865
I understand.

1578
01:47:08,236 --> 01:47:12,229
Well, tell me
if you know what effect, if any...

1579
01:47:12,476 --> 01:47:14,865
...these drugs
had on the relationship...

1580
01:47:15,116 --> 01:47:17,471
...between your friend Corinne
and Billy.

1581
01:47:17,716 --> 01:47:21,948
Well, now, when Billy got high,
he could be very, very hostile.

1582
01:47:22,676 --> 01:47:24,075
Hostile, when he was high.

1583
01:47:24,316 --> 01:47:27,114
Would you explain to the jury
what you mean by hostile?

1584
01:47:27,356 --> 01:47:30,587
I can do more than that, hon.
Let me show you something.

1585
01:47:30,836 --> 01:47:32,872
Look at my driver's license.

1586
01:47:33,116 --> 01:47:35,391
- Just a minute.
- Objection.

1587
01:47:35,716 --> 01:47:36,671
This isn't proper.

1588
01:47:36,916 --> 01:47:37,985
Be quiet.

1589
01:47:38,236 --> 01:47:39,271
I'll handle this.

1590
01:47:39,516 --> 01:47:40,392
Just a minute.

1591
01:47:40,636 --> 01:47:42,308
That's not proper procedure.

1592
01:47:44,156 --> 01:47:45,714
Pick up this item, please.

1593
01:47:46,676 --> 01:47:50,635
My eye. He hit me. I looked like
that dog from <i>The Little Rascals.</i>

1594
01:47:50,876 --> 01:47:54,551
Members of the jury, I'm instructing you
to disregard this outburst.

1595
01:47:54,796 --> 01:47:56,866
Pay no attention to that picture.

1596
01:47:58,156 --> 01:48:00,431
Your Honor? It's the truth.
I'm not lying.

1597
01:48:00,676 --> 01:48:02,587
Your Honor, the people...

1598
01:48:02,916 --> 01:48:03,951
Be quiet.

1599
01:48:04,196 --> 01:48:06,949
Now we got to get this thing
under control.

1600
01:48:07,196 --> 01:48:08,754
You sit down, Mr. De Veau.

1601
01:48:08,996 --> 01:48:11,146
Miss De Veau. I'm a single girl.

1602
01:48:11,516 --> 01:48:13,188
Miss De Veau, whatever.

1603
01:48:13,436 --> 01:48:14,391
Have a seat.

1604
01:48:15,156 --> 01:48:17,750
Okay, but please don't get too huffy.

1605
01:48:18,156 --> 01:48:19,748
You listen to me.

1606
01:48:20,956 --> 01:48:23,390
I'm in charge of this courtroom,
not you.

1607
01:48:23,636 --> 01:48:24,955
Here's the way it works:

1608
01:48:25,196 --> 01:48:28,074
These lawyers
are going to ask you questions...

1609
01:48:28,316 --> 01:48:29,715
...and you answer them.

1610
01:48:30,156 --> 01:48:32,067
If I tell you to stop, you stop.

1611
01:48:32,996 --> 01:48:34,987
If I tell you to sit, you sit.

1612
01:48:35,236 --> 01:48:38,592
And I don't want you to communicate
directly with that jury.

1613
01:48:38,836 --> 01:48:40,235
Don't produce any more items.

1614
01:48:40,756 --> 01:48:43,873
Don't show any photographs.
Do you understand that?

1615
01:48:45,436 --> 01:48:47,631
Yes, Your Honor.
I understand.

1616
01:48:52,156 --> 01:48:54,590
Mrs. Wright threw in some gumbo.

1617
01:48:55,716 --> 01:48:57,035
I got you cigarettes.

1618
01:48:58,396 --> 01:49:02,514
Thank you. How are we coming
with our character witnesses?

1619
01:49:02,756 --> 01:49:07,432
I thought we would limit it to 3 because
we don't need too much fawning and...

1620
01:49:08,076 --> 01:49:09,270
Why not?

1621
01:49:09,516 --> 01:49:11,950
Tell him how many friends
are lining up to defend me.

1622
01:49:12,196 --> 01:49:15,268
I suggest Wanda Javitz.
She has a commanding vocal presence.

1623
01:49:15,516 --> 01:49:17,666
She declined, Jim...

1624
01:49:17,916 --> 01:49:19,190
...along with some others.

1625
01:49:20,556 --> 01:49:21,705
Declined?

1626
01:49:26,996 --> 01:49:28,907
They clamored for my friendship.

1627
01:49:29,156 --> 01:49:32,353
Hoping and praying
for invitations to my parties.

1628
01:49:33,316 --> 01:49:35,227
Where were their judgments then?

1629
01:49:36,876 --> 01:49:40,471
I hope Wanda knows this puts her
in the out box for my Christmas party.

1630
01:49:41,796 --> 01:49:44,868
I don't think we have to worry
about character witnesses.

1631
01:49:45,116 --> 01:49:46,390
They got theirs, we got ours.

1632
01:49:47,356 --> 01:49:48,789
When do I take the stand?

1633
01:49:49,476 --> 01:49:50,431
Last.

1634
01:49:50,836 --> 01:49:51,825
Good.

1635
01:49:52,076 --> 01:49:55,466
They'll have heard all the theories.
We'll finish with the truth.

1636
01:49:55,716 --> 01:49:56,865
I look forward to this.

1637
01:49:57,116 --> 01:50:01,553
It's important, not that I'm acquitted,
but that everyone knows I'm innocent.

1638
01:50:03,276 --> 01:50:05,949
I refuse to live in a world
where whispers become fact.

1639
01:50:06,196 --> 01:50:09,074
Guilty men murmur.
The innocent shout to the rafters.

1640
01:50:09,316 --> 01:50:10,590
Hear, hear.

1641
01:50:11,636 --> 01:50:16,107
We may need you to come clean
about the relationship with Billy.

1642
01:50:17,996 --> 01:50:19,429
Your sexuality, Jim.

1643
01:50:20,196 --> 01:50:23,506
Finley's taken this thing in a direction
we didn't count on.

1644
01:50:23,756 --> 01:50:25,951
His own private witch-hunt.

1645
01:50:27,956 --> 01:50:29,833
It's going to destroy Mother.

1646
01:50:31,636 --> 01:50:33,115
Jim, she was in court.

1647
01:50:33,356 --> 01:50:34,709
She heard George Tucker.

1648
01:50:35,196 --> 01:50:37,232
Face it, she already knows.

1649
01:50:38,076 --> 01:50:39,907
Not from me she doesn't.

1650
01:50:46,756 --> 01:50:48,667
What if she wasn't in court?

1651
01:50:59,356 --> 01:51:01,347
What's the matter?
Gunpowder?

1652
01:51:04,116 --> 01:51:06,152
Damn gunshot residue test.

1653
01:51:06,396 --> 01:51:09,786
Your expert witness covered it.
He said the tests are unreliable.

1654
01:51:10,036 --> 01:51:11,833
Jury thinks that's a cop-out.

1655
01:51:12,316 --> 01:51:14,591
Every one of them knows Doc Poe.

1656
01:51:15,516 --> 01:51:18,588
Why listen to some egghead
from up north? No offense.

1657
01:51:18,836 --> 01:51:19,951
No, none taken.

1658
01:51:20,796 --> 01:51:24,391
He said gunpowder wipes off.
Maybe when they handled the body...

1659
01:51:24,636 --> 01:51:26,592
Boone says he bagged them.

1660
01:51:27,356 --> 01:51:31,031
Doc Poe says they were bagged
when he performed the autopsy.

1661
01:51:31,676 --> 01:51:33,871
When are they going to get wiped off?

1662
01:51:35,276 --> 01:51:36,470
I don't know.

1663
01:51:40,476 --> 01:51:44,230
Do you remember when you told me
that dead men tell no tales?

1664
01:51:45,916 --> 01:51:47,031
See, I think...

1665
01:51:47,276 --> 01:51:51,030
...that may be true,
but it does not apply here.

1666
01:51:51,636 --> 01:51:53,274
I mean, look around.

1667
01:51:54,596 --> 01:51:57,793
Every picture on every wall in this town
is of someone who's gone.

1668
01:51:58,036 --> 01:52:01,187
Every story you hear begins
with someone who's dead.

1669
01:52:02,076 --> 01:52:06,388
The only living national treasure
you have is your own slavering mutt.

1670
01:52:07,116 --> 01:52:11,189
You writing your book?
What the hell are you talking about?

1671
01:52:11,436 --> 01:52:14,189
Billy Hanson may not be talking,
but his hands are.

1672
01:52:14,676 --> 01:52:16,553
Billy Hanson's hands?

1673
01:52:19,676 --> 01:52:20,950
I got to go.

1674
01:52:23,236 --> 01:52:24,510
Where you going?

1675
01:52:27,796 --> 01:52:29,627
"To understand the living...

1676
01:52:30,076 --> 01:52:32,510
...you got to commune with the dead.

1677
01:52:33,116 --> 01:52:34,390
I need Shango.

1678
01:52:37,116 --> 01:52:38,265
Now go.

1679
01:52:38,516 --> 01:52:40,666
And don't you dare look back."

1680
01:52:42,156 --> 01:52:45,034
I hope you can communicate
with someone.

1681
01:52:50,876 --> 01:52:52,867
Feel like going for a walk?

1682
01:52:54,676 --> 01:52:56,029
Where you headed?

1683
01:52:57,036 --> 01:53:00,267
I don't know, I was thinking about
maybe stopping by the morgue.

1684
01:53:01,076 --> 01:53:02,794
Are you a necrophiliac or something?

1685
01:53:03,036 --> 01:53:05,152
We agreed you wouldn't talk
about my ex-wife.

1686
01:53:05,436 --> 01:53:08,269
- How long you been at the bar?
- Long enough. It'll be fun.

1687
01:53:08,516 --> 01:53:09,915
Why do you want to go?

1688
01:53:10,156 --> 01:53:12,989
If I could answer that question,
I wouldn't have to go.

1689
01:53:13,236 --> 01:53:17,070
The morgue's closed, and by tomorrow
this won't seem like such a good idea.

1690
01:53:17,316 --> 01:53:22,026
Precisely. I'll break in if I have to.
I don't care. I'll pretend I'm dead.

1691
01:53:22,796 --> 01:53:25,310
- You sure you want to do this?
- I think so.

1692
01:53:26,236 --> 01:53:28,545
There is a back way...

1693
01:53:28,796 --> 01:53:31,515
...a hallway off the emergency room.
It's off-limits.

1694
01:53:31,756 --> 01:53:34,031
- How do you know that?
- I candy-striped one summer.

1695
01:53:34,276 --> 01:53:35,675
At the morgue?

1696
01:53:36,036 --> 01:53:38,231
- We'll create a distraction...
- We?

1697
01:53:38,476 --> 01:53:42,435
You create the distraction
and I'll just slip in and check it out.

1698
01:53:44,076 --> 01:53:45,748
No, you'll get lost.

1699
01:53:46,356 --> 01:53:48,916
All right, it's a 3-man job.
Where's Joe?

1700
01:53:49,156 --> 01:53:52,273
Perfect casting, but he's out of town
till tomorrow.

1701
01:53:53,916 --> 01:53:56,066
Who do we know
who can cause a commotion?

1702
01:54:03,676 --> 01:54:04,950
Hello! Nurse!

1703
01:54:09,036 --> 01:54:10,515
- What's wrong with her?
- Her stomach.

1704
01:54:10,756 --> 01:54:12,348
Appendicitis.
My water broke.

1705
01:54:12,596 --> 01:54:15,554
Get the doctor to exam 4.
Water broke? She's pregnant.

1706
01:54:15,796 --> 01:54:17,787
I don't know what's up. Just help.

1707
01:54:18,036 --> 01:54:20,152
- What's wrong?
- A stomach problem.

1708
01:54:20,396 --> 01:54:22,068
Let's get her up on the table.

1709
01:54:28,876 --> 01:54:30,150
Okay, here we are.

1710
01:54:30,396 --> 01:54:31,954
Commune away.

1711
01:54:32,196 --> 01:54:33,390
Is this where it hurts?

1712
01:54:33,636 --> 01:54:35,115
Just...
Oh, doctor, wait.

1713
01:54:35,916 --> 01:54:36,792
Here?

1714
01:54:37,036 --> 01:54:39,755
You know, I think you need to go
just a little bit lower.

1715
01:54:40,596 --> 01:54:41,665
Never been in a morgue.

1716
01:54:41,916 --> 01:54:43,349
What are we looking for?

1717
01:54:45,356 --> 01:54:48,712
I don't know. Something about
the bagging of the hands.

1718
01:54:49,196 --> 01:54:51,266
Oh, look. Teddy Lipscomb.

1719
01:54:52,076 --> 01:54:53,191
Excuse me?

1720
01:54:53,716 --> 01:54:56,833
- You know this guy?
- Yeah, he was my dad's dentist.

1721
01:54:57,556 --> 01:54:59,194
Oh, man!

1722
01:55:00,836 --> 01:55:01,712
Cardiac arrest.

1723
01:55:01,956 --> 01:55:06,347
Right. Medical term for dying in the
arms of a 25-year-old cocktail waitress.

1724
01:55:06,596 --> 01:55:07,346
Poor guy.

1725
01:55:09,436 --> 01:55:12,667
See, now, remind me
never to get sick in Savannah.

1726
01:55:12,916 --> 01:55:14,827
He's wearing a hospital I.D. Bracelet.

1727
01:55:15,076 --> 01:55:17,874
You're supposed to get well
in hospitals, but not in this city.

1728
01:55:18,196 --> 01:55:22,474
The morgue doesn't have its own ramp,
so all DOA's come through emergency.

1729
01:55:22,716 --> 01:55:24,946
Technically, they'd have to be admitted.

1730
01:55:27,556 --> 01:55:28,875
They're all wearing bracelets.

1731
01:55:29,116 --> 01:55:32,074
It's bureaucratic red tape.
I told you, I candy-striped.

1732
01:55:32,316 --> 01:55:34,227
You did.
That's like volunteer work?

1733
01:55:34,476 --> 01:55:36,751
Yeah, cute little striped outfit,
short skirt.

1734
01:55:36,996 --> 01:55:38,065
Girl Scouts.

1735
01:55:38,796 --> 01:55:40,468
- Is this where it hurts?
- Almost.

1736
01:55:40,716 --> 01:55:42,832
Just a tad bit...

1737
01:55:43,076 --> 01:55:45,636
That's the spot.
I love you.

1738
01:55:45,916 --> 01:55:49,113
I love you.
Oh, Dr. Feelgood, that's the spot.

1739
01:55:49,356 --> 01:55:50,550
You got it.

1740
01:55:55,876 --> 01:55:59,915
You wouldn't take a bag off
to put an I.D. Bracelet on, would you?

1741
01:56:00,756 --> 01:56:02,075
Yeah, probably.

1742
01:56:02,316 --> 01:56:03,271
Maybe.

1743
01:56:07,716 --> 01:56:10,469
Pleasure's been all mine, Doctor.

1744
01:56:10,956 --> 01:56:11,991
How you doing, Mom?

1745
01:56:12,236 --> 01:56:14,511
Nurse, I have a question for you.

1746
01:56:14,756 --> 01:56:17,509
Were you on duty the night
Billy Hanson's body came in?

1747
01:56:17,756 --> 01:56:19,428
I was.
How'd you get back there?

1748
01:56:19,676 --> 01:56:22,236
Back door.
I was here with the sick lady?

1749
01:56:22,476 --> 01:56:25,388
I have a question.
Hanson's hands were bagged.

1750
01:56:25,636 --> 01:56:27,274
Someone had to put the I.D. Bracelet on.

1751
01:56:27,516 --> 01:56:30,314
Would you take the bag off
to slide the bracelet on?

1752
01:56:30,556 --> 01:56:32,387
No, they snap on.

1753
01:56:33,356 --> 01:56:34,675
They snap on?

1754
01:56:36,476 --> 01:56:37,386
Thank you.

1755
01:56:37,636 --> 01:56:40,389
It was easier with him
because I bagged him after.

1756
01:56:43,436 --> 01:56:44,551
Excuse me?

1757
01:56:45,116 --> 01:56:49,587
Doc Poe called from the crime scene and
said to bag the hands when he came in.

1758
01:56:51,636 --> 01:56:52,989
You bagged the hands?

1759
01:56:53,436 --> 01:56:55,950
Yes, I wrote it up
on the admission sheet.

1760
01:56:56,196 --> 01:56:57,345
May I see that?

1761
01:57:00,156 --> 01:57:02,306
We'll let Sonny tell you.
He'll be here any minute.

1762
01:57:02,556 --> 01:57:06,071
Before Sonny gets here,
I'd like to run something by you.

1763
01:57:06,316 --> 01:57:08,466
- Fire away.
- About that night.

1764
01:57:15,956 --> 01:57:17,309
What do you got?

1765
01:57:19,076 --> 01:57:21,636
The evening started out
as I've always said.

1766
01:57:22,756 --> 01:57:23,825
<i>The argument...</i>

1767
01:57:24,236 --> 01:57:25,351
<i>... the shouting...</i>

1768
01:57:28,956 --> 01:57:30,947
You let me down, like everyone else.

1769
01:57:31,796 --> 01:57:35,391
My mama let me down. She hates me
because I look like my daddy.

1770
01:57:35,636 --> 01:57:38,070
- What are you yelling about?
- I'm yelling about you!

1771
01:57:38,316 --> 01:57:42,434
It's fine for you to talk to me
about living in this grandeur and all.

1772
01:57:42,676 --> 01:57:44,667
You could do it
if you took responsibility.

1773
01:57:44,916 --> 01:57:46,429
Bullshit, Jim!

1774
01:57:46,676 --> 01:57:49,713
If you don't like it,
why don't you just get the hell out?!

1775
01:57:49,996 --> 01:57:51,349
Get the hell out.

1776
01:57:51,596 --> 01:57:54,315
This candle is about ready
to go through that painting!

1777
01:57:54,556 --> 01:57:58,344
I'll stop paying the insurance
on your Camaro.

1778
01:57:58,596 --> 01:58:02,271
You want to leave,
you can do it tomorrow morning.

1779
01:58:05,116 --> 01:58:06,549
<i>The damaged clock...</i>

1780
01:58:17,596 --> 01:58:18,745
Goddamn it.

1781
01:58:18,996 --> 01:58:22,147
Walk into my house
and ruin my furniture. I've had it.

1782
01:58:22,396 --> 01:58:24,990
You're going to jail, young man.
That's it.

1783
01:58:26,396 --> 01:58:28,148
<i>Billy pointing the Luger...</i>

1784
01:58:28,396 --> 01:58:29,875
I may be leaving tomorrow...

1785
01:58:30,756 --> 01:58:31,871
...but goddamn it...

1786
01:58:32,236 --> 01:58:35,034
<i>But here's the difference:</i>
<i>When he pulled the trigger...</i>

1787
01:58:35,276 --> 01:58:36,152
...you're leaving tonight.

1788
01:58:37,116 --> 01:58:38,151
<i>... nothing happened.</i>

1789
01:58:38,396 --> 01:58:40,512
<i>The gun was on safety.</i>

1790
01:58:40,756 --> 01:58:43,907
<i>As he fumbled to take the safety off,</i>
<i>I grabbed my own gun...</i>

1791
01:58:49,716 --> 01:58:50,944
<i>... and I shot him.</i>

1792
01:59:06,876 --> 01:59:08,150
He fell dead.

1793
01:59:13,436 --> 01:59:15,267
He never fired?

1794
01:59:16,916 --> 01:59:17,871
No.

1795
01:59:19,036 --> 01:59:21,504
<i>I thought, "What have you done?!"</i>

1796
01:59:51,356 --> 01:59:52,994
It explains...

1797
01:59:53,236 --> 01:59:56,273
...why there's no powder
on Billy's hands.

1798
01:59:56,516 --> 01:59:59,952
When I sit on that stand
and I tell this to the jury...

1799
02:00:00,196 --> 02:00:01,675
...Largent's case...

1800
02:00:01,916 --> 02:00:03,634
...will crumble.

1801
02:00:10,756 --> 02:00:12,633
I don't see how you figure that.

1802
02:00:14,556 --> 02:00:16,308
If you tell that story...

1803
02:00:16,836 --> 02:00:18,155
...you're admitting...

1804
02:00:18,396 --> 02:00:19,624
...that you lied.

1805
02:00:21,956 --> 02:00:23,105
Lied to everyone.

1806
02:00:23,356 --> 02:00:24,675
The police...

1807
02:00:25,036 --> 02:00:26,389
...the press...

1808
02:00:28,076 --> 02:00:29,350
...everyone.

1809
02:00:32,316 --> 02:00:33,385
Yes.

1810
02:00:35,036 --> 02:00:36,389
Of course.

1811
02:00:38,556 --> 02:00:42,947
I'd rather be convicted of lying
than of murder.

1812
02:00:44,956 --> 02:00:45,911
So...

1813
02:00:46,916 --> 02:00:47,985
Hey, coach.

1814
02:00:48,236 --> 02:00:49,385
We got it.

1815
02:00:50,836 --> 02:00:51,825
Keep your seat.

1816
02:00:52,556 --> 02:00:54,547
Sonny, I need to tell you something.

1817
02:00:55,036 --> 02:00:58,312
Now, me first.
You know that gunshot residue test?

1818
02:00:58,556 --> 02:01:01,309
What I have to say has direct bearing
on the gunshot residue...

1819
02:01:01,556 --> 02:01:02,830
Can I get this out?

1820
02:01:06,476 --> 02:01:08,194
We got them by the gonads.

1821
02:01:08,436 --> 02:01:10,313
Detective Boone lied.

1822
02:01:11,356 --> 02:01:15,713
Doc Poe called the admitting nurse
and told her to bag the hands...

1823
02:01:15,956 --> 02:01:17,708
...if they were not already.

1824
02:01:17,956 --> 02:01:19,514
Which she did.

1825
02:01:19,796 --> 02:01:21,195
Right here in this document.

1826
02:01:26,876 --> 02:01:31,233
Many could have handled the body
between the crime scene and the hospital.

1827
02:01:31,956 --> 02:01:34,265
Which explains how the powder
got rubbed off.

1828
02:01:34,996 --> 02:01:36,145
There it is.

1829
02:01:37,036 --> 02:01:41,712
The death knell to Finley Largent's
precious gunshot residue test.

1830
02:01:45,196 --> 02:01:46,231
Your turn.

1831
02:01:47,116 --> 02:01:48,151
What was it?

1832
02:01:52,396 --> 02:01:53,988
Oh, it's not important.

1833
02:02:00,796 --> 02:02:02,070
Take a look here.

1834
02:02:03,116 --> 02:02:05,027
We got them, Jimbo.

1835
02:02:13,476 --> 02:02:15,068
Going somewhere, coach?

1836
02:02:23,396 --> 02:02:24,875
What's his story?

1837
02:02:45,156 --> 02:02:46,953
You're still under oath.

1838
02:02:47,676 --> 02:02:48,586
Frank...

1839
02:02:49,756 --> 02:02:52,031
...are you absolutely sure...

1840
02:02:52,276 --> 02:02:55,586
...that you bagged Billy Hanson's hands
at Mercer House?

1841
02:02:55,836 --> 02:02:56,951
Yes.

1842
02:03:00,516 --> 02:03:02,586
I have no further questions.

1843
02:03:03,156 --> 02:03:05,067
Redirect, Mr. Largent?

1844
02:03:09,396 --> 02:03:10,431
No, Your Honor.

1845
02:03:11,236 --> 02:03:15,787
Detective, you're excused. You're still
under subpoena. Thank you very much.

1846
02:03:16,276 --> 02:03:18,836
Defense calls Sara Warren...

1847
02:03:19,076 --> 02:03:20,191
...R.N.

1848
02:03:25,276 --> 02:03:27,028
You won't find her in your notes.

1849
02:03:27,276 --> 02:03:29,107
She's not on your list, Finley.

1850
02:03:29,356 --> 02:03:33,474
Sara Warren is a direct rebuttal
to the testimony of Detective Boone.

1851
02:03:34,396 --> 02:03:36,591
She is, in fact, an admitting nurse...

1852
02:03:36,836 --> 02:03:38,428
...at Chandler Emergency Room.

1853
02:03:58,996 --> 02:04:03,467
<i>Mr. Williams, will you describe</i>
<i>your relationship with the deceased?</i>

1854
02:04:05,716 --> 02:04:09,868
I met Billy Hanson when he came around
to the house wanting a job.

1855
02:04:10,796 --> 02:04:11,706
So...

1856
02:04:11,956 --> 02:04:14,424
...I hired him in the workshop
to refinish furniture.

1857
02:04:14,676 --> 02:04:17,190
He had some talent,
and I wanted to encourage him.

1858
02:04:17,716 --> 02:04:18,990
During this time...

1859
02:04:19,236 --> 02:04:23,024
...I developed hypoglycemia. I
blacked-out at times. I don't eat well.

1860
02:04:23,276 --> 02:04:24,948
The doctor told me...

1861
02:04:25,196 --> 02:04:28,586
...it was not good for me to be alone
when this condition occurs.

1862
02:04:28,836 --> 02:04:30,633
So Billy would stay over...

1863
02:04:30,876 --> 02:04:32,628
...and take care of me
when I wasn't well.

1864
02:04:32,876 --> 02:04:36,073
He did not live at Mercer House,
as has been stated.

1865
02:04:39,116 --> 02:04:43,906
Is that the full extent of your
relationship with Billy Hanson?

1866
02:04:45,876 --> 02:04:50,154
No. Over time, it evolved
into something less formal.

1867
02:04:51,076 --> 02:04:52,225
We became intimate.

1868
02:04:52,916 --> 02:04:54,747
Billy could be very charming.

1869
02:04:54,996 --> 02:04:57,351
He had his girlfriends and I had mine.

1870
02:04:57,836 --> 02:04:58,825
But to me...

1871
02:04:59,076 --> 02:05:01,431
...sex is a perfectly natural thing.

1872
02:05:01,756 --> 02:05:03,712
It didn't bother me.
It didn't bother him.

1873
02:05:04,276 --> 02:05:08,792
It was just an occasional natural
occurrence between consenting adults.

1874
02:05:14,476 --> 02:05:16,387
Would you describe to the jury...

1875
02:05:16,636 --> 02:05:19,389
...the events
that occurred in your house...

1876
02:05:19,636 --> 02:05:20,910
...after the party?

1877
02:05:23,116 --> 02:05:25,994
By the time Billy got back to the house
he was quite high...

1878
02:05:26,236 --> 02:05:29,069
...and we got into an argument
about a planned trip to London.

1879
02:05:29,476 --> 02:05:33,230
I was going to an auction, and Billy was
to accompany me because of my condition.

1880
02:05:34,716 --> 02:05:37,071
But he insisted on taking
marijuana cigarettes.

1881
02:05:37,316 --> 02:05:40,786
I do not approve of drugs
and I told him he could not go.

1882
02:05:41,036 --> 02:05:43,914
He became verbally abusive
and I ordered Billy out of the house.

1883
02:05:44,156 --> 02:05:45,509
He went into the hallway.

1884
02:05:45,756 --> 02:05:49,590
The argument continued there.
Then he knocked over a clock.

1885
02:05:50,756 --> 02:05:54,112
I went to call the police.
He followed me with a gun.

1886
02:05:54,356 --> 02:05:55,471
<i>He said...</i>

1887
02:05:56,996 --> 02:05:58,907
...and I'll never forget this:

1888
02:05:59,156 --> 02:06:00,555
<i>"I might leave tomorrow...</i>

1889
02:06:00,796 --> 02:06:03,264
...but goddamn it,
you're leaving tonight."

1890
02:06:05,716 --> 02:06:06,785
I saw that Luger...

1891
02:06:07,036 --> 02:06:07,832
<i>... and moved.</i>

1892
02:06:08,076 --> 02:06:10,192
I reached in a drawer
for my own weapon.

1893
02:06:10,436 --> 02:06:12,188
As I came up,
the first shot...

1894
02:06:12,756 --> 02:06:14,314
<i>... I felt breeze by my shoulder.</i>

1895
02:06:18,756 --> 02:06:19,745
And I fired.

1896
02:06:23,236 --> 02:06:24,749
I don't remember how many times.

1897
02:06:27,436 --> 02:06:28,915
<i>It was horrible.</i>

1898
02:06:53,516 --> 02:06:55,393
<i>We're all Savannahians.</i>

1899
02:06:55,636 --> 02:06:58,787
<i>Our paths cross from time to time.</i>

1900
02:06:59,276 --> 02:07:00,709
<i>We greet each other.</i>

1901
02:07:01,156 --> 02:07:03,226
<i>Smile here, nod there.</i>

1902
02:07:04,196 --> 02:07:06,152
<i>But even if we don 't know each other...</i>

1903
02:07:06,916 --> 02:07:08,668
<i>... we have one thing in common.</i>

1904
02:07:09,876 --> 02:07:12,709
<i>This beautiful place where we all live.</i>

1905
02:07:13,796 --> 02:07:15,468
<i>And as one Savannahian...</i>

1906
02:07:15,716 --> 02:07:16,865
<i>... to 12...</i>

1907
02:07:17,716 --> 02:07:21,152
<i>... I'd like to thank you</i>
<i>for your civic pride...</i>

1908
02:07:21,516 --> 02:07:22,949
<i>... for your diligence...</i>

1909
02:07:23,396 --> 02:07:25,193
<i>... and here in this courtroom...</i>

1910
02:07:25,676 --> 02:07:27,234
<i>... for your rapt attention.</i>

1911
02:07:27,476 --> 02:07:29,512
I've watched you taking notes.

1912
02:07:30,676 --> 02:07:33,634
The prosecution
started this whole thing...

1913
02:07:33,876 --> 02:07:36,344
...quoting someone
by the name of Hobbes.

1914
02:07:36,596 --> 02:07:38,029
I don't know who that is...

1915
02:07:39,276 --> 02:07:40,072
...but...

1916
02:07:40,356 --> 02:07:42,950
...I do know who Perry Mason is.

1917
02:07:43,636 --> 02:07:44,705
You watch <i>Perry Mason</i>?

1918
02:07:45,996 --> 02:07:46,985
I do.

1919
02:07:47,916 --> 02:07:49,269
And I got to thinking...

1920
02:07:49,516 --> 02:07:51,427
...if some TV writer...

1921
02:07:51,956 --> 02:07:53,947
...was to come to Perry Mason
and say...

1922
02:07:54,196 --> 02:07:58,030
..."Here you are, Mr. Raymond Burr,
here's a story like this."

1923
02:07:58,276 --> 02:07:59,948
You know what I think he'd say?

1924
02:08:00,196 --> 02:08:01,948
I think old Raymond would say...

1925
02:08:02,116 --> 02:08:04,584
"That's not a very good story.

1926
02:08:04,836 --> 02:08:07,350
I wouldn't have to be
a very good lawyer...

1927
02:08:07,596 --> 02:08:09,791
...to get that man off,
now would I?"

1928
02:08:10,636 --> 02:08:11,785
He'd be right!

1929
02:08:13,796 --> 02:08:14,785
Because...

1930
02:08:15,076 --> 02:08:18,910
...by all the evidence,
Jim Williams is an innocent man.

1931
02:08:20,676 --> 02:08:22,268
But I'm not Perry Mason.

1932
02:08:23,716 --> 02:08:25,672
I'm not some TV lawyer.

1933
02:08:26,876 --> 02:08:31,586
So I got to scratch and tear
at the prosecution's case...

1934
02:08:32,356 --> 02:08:35,189
...trying to whittle it down to nothing.

1935
02:08:35,836 --> 02:08:37,986
And darned if I don't think I have!

1936
02:08:39,836 --> 02:08:44,466
Because the fabrication
of the prosecution's case is in pieces.

1937
02:08:44,756 --> 02:08:47,429
When you consider
how Detective Boone...

1938
02:08:47,676 --> 02:08:51,908
...has consistently lied
about bagging the hands.

1939
02:08:55,476 --> 02:08:57,034
Does that surprise you...

1940
02:08:58,036 --> 02:08:59,788
...that a detective would lie?

1941
02:09:01,236 --> 02:09:02,874
Of course he will.

1942
02:09:03,476 --> 02:09:04,989
He's not a bad man.

1943
02:09:05,236 --> 02:09:07,511
But how else will he play the cards...

1944
02:09:07,796 --> 02:09:10,435
...that have been dealt to him
from a pack of lies?

1945
02:09:12,956 --> 02:09:14,230
If Jim Williams...

1946
02:09:14,916 --> 02:09:16,634
...is guilty of anything...

1947
02:09:17,676 --> 02:09:19,871
...he's guilty of bad association.

1948
02:09:21,276 --> 02:09:23,665
But that's not why he's on trial for.

1949
02:09:24,676 --> 02:09:26,348
If you don't like...

1950
02:09:26,596 --> 02:09:30,066
...or if you don't cotton
to his lifestyle...

1951
02:09:30,596 --> 02:09:32,188
...just think about this:

1952
02:09:32,796 --> 02:09:34,787
We deal with these people all the time.

1953
02:09:35,116 --> 02:09:36,151
Some good...

1954
02:09:36,396 --> 02:09:37,670
...some bad.

1955
02:09:39,196 --> 02:09:40,834
They're a part of our community.

1956
02:09:42,596 --> 02:09:44,712
You can't judge a man for that.

1957
02:09:45,636 --> 02:09:47,035
This is God's world.

1958
02:09:47,996 --> 02:09:49,907
Let God be the judge of that.

1959
02:09:51,556 --> 02:09:53,035
And let you good folks...

1960
02:09:54,076 --> 02:09:55,668
...be the judge of this.

1961
02:09:58,276 --> 02:09:59,550
Come on, now.

1962
02:10:02,636 --> 02:10:04,354
You let this man go home.

1963
02:10:08,556 --> 02:10:09,784
He's had enough.

1964
02:10:16,316 --> 02:10:17,431
Thank you.

1965
02:10:54,156 --> 02:10:57,466
Mr. Foreman,
has the jury reached a verdict?

1966
02:10:58,236 --> 02:10:59,749
Yes, we have, Your Honor.

1967
02:11:00,476 --> 02:11:01,704
Is it unanimous?

1968
02:11:02,796 --> 02:11:03,865
Yes!

1969
02:11:08,276 --> 02:11:09,914
Hand it to the sheriff, please.

1970
02:11:22,556 --> 02:11:24,035
Pick that up.

1971
02:11:28,356 --> 02:11:29,709
Hand it to me.

1972
02:11:37,916 --> 02:11:39,474
Give it back to him.

1973
02:11:50,396 --> 02:11:52,956
Defendant and attorneys,
rise, please.

1974
02:11:56,396 --> 02:11:57,988
Publish the verdict.

1975
02:12:00,476 --> 02:12:03,115
"We, the jury,
find the defendant...

1976
02:12:04,476 --> 02:12:05,511
...not guilty."

1977
02:12:14,676 --> 02:12:17,509
Members of the jury,
this concludes your work.

1978
02:12:17,756 --> 02:12:21,715
You've rendered great service
to Savannah and Chatham County.

1979
02:12:21,996 --> 02:12:24,829
I'm going to dismiss you now
with the thanks of the court.

1980
02:12:38,476 --> 02:12:39,704
Congratulations, Jim.

1981
02:12:39,956 --> 02:12:41,105
Thank you, John.

1982
02:13:12,116 --> 02:13:13,435
Hey, boy!

1983
02:13:18,396 --> 02:13:19,795
What do you got?

1984
02:13:20,756 --> 02:13:22,155
Come on down.

1985
02:13:23,196 --> 02:13:25,266
We gots to go visit the boy.

1986
02:13:28,716 --> 02:13:31,276
We got to make him
quit working James.

1987
02:13:31,996 --> 02:13:33,873
Trial's over, Minerva.

1988
02:13:34,556 --> 02:13:36,751
Billy can't do anything to James now.

1989
02:13:37,796 --> 02:13:39,388
Why I come to you?

1990
02:13:40,196 --> 02:13:41,754
Because you...

1991
02:13:41,996 --> 02:13:44,510
...out of everybody,
know it ain't over yet.

1992
02:13:46,156 --> 02:13:51,184
I know, the boy know, and you know
justice ain't been done yet.

1993
02:13:57,236 --> 02:13:58,874
I'll come down for a minute.

1994
02:14:01,916 --> 02:14:03,429
I don't know about this.

1995
02:14:03,676 --> 02:14:06,509
That's exactly why you come this far.

1996
02:14:32,996 --> 02:14:35,829
Billy always loved Wild Turkey.

1997
02:14:36,676 --> 02:14:38,348
He ain't happy here.

1998
02:14:41,316 --> 02:14:43,147
Ain't what he thought it would be.

1999
02:14:45,836 --> 02:14:49,146
If you ain't in heaven yet, you want
to get there, don't you, boy?

2000
02:14:51,836 --> 02:14:54,908
The only way you're going to get up...

2001
02:14:55,156 --> 02:14:57,624
...is if you quit playing with James.

2002
02:15:10,196 --> 02:15:12,630
I has influence with the dead.

2003
02:15:12,876 --> 02:15:14,707
They can lift you up.

2004
02:15:14,956 --> 02:15:18,073
Nobody else can do that for you.
Nobody!

2005
02:15:26,516 --> 02:15:28,268
Don't you laugh at me!

2006
02:15:28,956 --> 02:15:31,231
You think you had a harsh life?

2007
02:15:31,476 --> 02:15:33,546
You got no idea.

2008
02:15:37,556 --> 02:15:40,116
Never had no bills to pay...

2009
02:15:40,436 --> 02:15:43,473
...no children to feed,
no house to clean.

2010
02:15:44,876 --> 02:15:46,867
You had it easy.

2011
02:15:49,196 --> 02:15:51,551
You can just lay there.

2012
02:16:24,036 --> 02:16:25,185
Where's Jim?

2013
02:16:41,956 --> 02:16:43,708
Thanks for dropping by.

2014
02:16:47,076 --> 02:16:50,751
I've finished my Christmas party list...

2015
02:16:53,116 --> 02:16:54,026
...and you made the cut.

2016
02:16:54,276 --> 02:16:56,665
I'm honored,
but I won't be here.

2017
02:16:57,116 --> 02:16:59,186
Many will be disappointed.

2018
02:17:00,316 --> 02:17:02,750
So, obviously,
you've decided to stay in town.

2019
02:17:04,476 --> 02:17:07,354
Living here pisses off
all the right people.

2020
02:17:09,116 --> 02:17:12,233
- What can I do for you?
- I have something for you.

2021
02:17:12,476 --> 02:17:15,309
Yussopov's dagger may have seemed...

2022
02:17:15,556 --> 02:17:17,706
...more useful,
given your profession...

2023
02:17:17,956 --> 02:17:20,516
...but the painting
somehow seemed appropriate.

2024
02:17:20,756 --> 02:17:22,792
I hope you will accept it...

2025
02:17:23,036 --> 02:17:24,947
...as an expression of my gratitude.

2026
02:17:25,196 --> 02:17:26,834
<i>Newmarket Heath,</i> the overpaint.

2027
02:17:28,076 --> 02:17:28,952
Thank you.

2028
02:17:29,196 --> 02:17:31,551
I'll have it sent along.

2029
02:17:33,036 --> 02:17:35,345
I don't want to keep you
from your party.

2030
02:17:38,956 --> 02:17:41,789
But one more question, for the book.

2031
02:17:44,476 --> 02:17:46,387
Do you want to tell me
what really happened?

2032
02:17:52,836 --> 02:17:53,905
Sport...

2033
02:17:55,436 --> 02:17:57,711
...truth, like art...

2034
02:17:57,956 --> 02:17:59,867
...is in the eye of the beholder.

2035
02:18:02,956 --> 02:18:04,708
You believe what you choose...

2036
02:18:05,796 --> 02:18:07,707
...and I'll believe what I know.

2037
02:18:09,116 --> 02:18:10,390
Good luck, Jim.

2038
02:20:38,916 --> 02:20:40,269
Why didn't you come in?

2039
02:20:41,556 --> 02:20:44,070
I never enter the office on Sunday.

2040
02:20:44,316 --> 02:20:45,385
Bad juju.

2041
02:20:47,076 --> 02:20:48,794
I still got a lot of questions.

2042
02:20:50,756 --> 02:20:52,474
You know all you need to know.

2043
02:20:53,236 --> 02:20:54,510
One thing...

2044
02:20:54,916 --> 02:20:57,749
...don't commune so long with the dead
you forget the living.

2045
02:21:02,396 --> 02:21:03,670
What's this?

2046
02:21:14,716 --> 02:21:16,149
I love you, boy.

2047
02:21:16,916 --> 02:21:20,113
But I ain't the only one.
You know that, don't you?

2048
02:21:39,356 --> 02:21:41,074
How long's your lease?

2049
02:21:43,196 --> 02:21:44,595
Six months.

2050
02:21:46,996 --> 02:21:48,668
Welcome to Savannah.

2051
02:21:49,396 --> 02:21:50,272
You hungry?

2052
02:21:50,516 --> 02:21:52,427
- Come on.
- Let's go, girl.

2053
02:22:01,116 --> 02:22:04,426
You two know you're not going anywhere
without a chaperone.

2054
02:22:04,676 --> 02:22:08,954
I cooked my Chablis' famous chicken.
Let's go have a picnic.

2055
02:22:10,036 --> 02:22:11,264
And guess what?

2056
02:22:11,516 --> 02:22:14,269
You get your choice of breast or thigh.

2057
02:22:14,876 --> 02:22:16,673
What's it called, the chicken?

2058
02:22:17,076 --> 02:22:19,192
Chablis' Kicking Chicken.

2059
02:22:25,436 --> 02:22:26,994
Still walking the dog, Mr. Glover?

2060
02:22:27,236 --> 02:22:29,796
Yes, sir.
Patrick do like his morning walk.

2061
02:22:31,476 --> 02:22:34,707
Patrick is walking kind of fancy
this morning, isn't he?